subject: College Athletics
lead_paragraph: Top-ranked Iowa advanced 7 of 9 qualifiers and held a 1-point lead after the first round of the N.C.A.A. championship in St. Louis. Iowa, 21-1 in dual meets this season, had 18 points. The Hawkeyes are seeking their 21st title, but first since 2000. Central Michigan was second with 17 points and Iowa State third with 16. Simultaneous competition was held on eight rings, with 170 matches completed in about three and a half hours.
